article.description: Otis Livingston II scored 16 of his career-high 22 points in the second half, Marquise Moore had his fourth double-double in six games this season and George Mason pulled away in the second half
article.headline: Livingston scores 22, George Mason beats Bradley 77-66
article.linkText: Livingston scores 22, George Mason beats Bradley 77-66
article.story: ESTERO, Fla. -- Otis Livingston II scored 16 of his career-high 22 points in the second half, Marquise Moore had his fourth double-double in six games this season and George Mason pulled away in the second half for a 77-66 win over Bradley on Wednesday. Livingston made 8 of 13 field goals, Moore finished with 17 points, a season-high 15 rebounds and five assists and freshman guard Justin Kier had eight points and a career-best 10 rebounds. George Mason (3-3) scored 14-straight points, including two 3s by Livingston, to take a 41-29 lead with 15:13 left. A 3-pointer by Karmari Newman sparked a 9-1 run that made it 57-40 about six minutes later and the Patriots led by double figures the rest of the way. Darrell Brown scored 15 and Antoine Pittman added 12 points for Bradley (3-3). George Mason outrebounded the Braves 50-35 and made 23 of 31 free throws. Bradley hit just 11 of 21 foul shots.
